President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Ohio and authorized Federal assistance to support recovery efforts from severe storms, flooding, and landslides that occurred from February 14 to February 25, 2018. Federal funding will be available to the State, local governments, and certain nonprofit organizations for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. The affected counties include Adams, Athens, Belmont, Brown, Columbiana, Gallia, Hamilton, Jackson, Lawrence, Meigs, Monroe, Muskingum, Noble, Perry, Pike, Scioto, Vinton, and Washington. Hazard mitigation measures will also receive Federal funding statewide. Steven Johnson has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations, and additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.